## Context Management

### Provider Hierarchy
```
<AuthProvider>
  <ToastProvider>
    <StudentActivityProvider>
      <QuestionBankProvider>
        <AssignmentProvider>
          <VocabularyProvider>
            {children}
          </VocabularyProvider>
        </AssignmentProvider>
      </QuestionBankProvider>
    </StudentActivityProvider>
  </ToastProvider>
</AuthProvider>
```

### Custom Hooks Pattern
```typescript
export function useCustomContext() {
  const context = useContext(CustomContext)
  if (!context) {
    throw new Error('useCustomContext must be used within CustomProvider')
  }
  return context
}
```

## Performance Optimization

### React Optimization
```typescript
// Memoize expensive computations
const expensiveResult = useMemo(() => {
  return computeExpensiveValue(data)
}, [data])

// Memoize callbacks
const handleClick = useCallback((id: string) => {
  performAction(id)
}, [performAction])

// Memoize components
const MemoizedComponent = memo(ExpensiveComponent)
```

### Image Optimization
```typescript
import Image from 'next/image'

<Image
  src="/physics-diagram.png"
  alt="Physics diagram"
  width={800}
  height={600}
  priority={isAboveFold}
  placeholder="blur"
  blurDataURL={blurDataUrl}
/>
```

## AI Integration

### OpenAI Patterns
```typescript
const generatePhysicsQuestion = async (topic: string, level: string) => {
  const prompt = `
    Generate a ${level} difficulty physics question about ${topic}.
    Requirements:
    - Use proper physics notation and units
    - Include a clear problem statement
    - Provide step-by-step solution
    - Focus on conceptual understanding
  `
  
  const response = await openai.chat.completions.create({
    model: "gpt-4",
    messages: [{ role: "user", content: prompt }],
    temperature: 0.7,
    max_tokens: 500
  })
  
  return response.choices[0].message.content
}
```

## Testing Guidelines

### Test Structure
```typescript
import { render, screen, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react'
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event'

describe('ComponentName', () => {
  it('should handle user interaction', async () => {
    const user = userEvent.setup()
    const mockHandler = jest.fn()
    
    render(<ComponentName onAction={mockHandler} />)
    
    await user.click(screen.getByRole('button'))
    
    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(mockHandler).toHaveBeenCalledWith(expectedData)
    })
  })
})
```

## Accessibility Requirements

### ARIA Labels
```typescript
<button
  aria-label="Delete assignment"
  aria-describedby="delete-warning"
  onClick={handleDelete}
>
  <Trash2 className="h-4 w-4" />
</button>
<span id="delete-warning" className="sr-only">
  This action cannot be undone
</span>
```

### Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Use proper focus management
- Implement skip links for navigation
- Test with screen readers

## File Organization

### Directory Structure
```
src/
├── app/                  # Next.js App Router
│   ├── (auth)/          # Auth group routes
│   ├── admin/           # Admin routes
│   ├── api/             # API routes
│   └── simulations/     # Interactive simulations
├── components/          # React components
│   ├── admin/           # Admin components
│   ├── simulations/     # Simulation components
│   └── ui/              # shadcn/ui base
├── contexts/            # Context providers
├── hooks/               # Custom React hooks
├── lib/                 # Core utilities
├── types/               # TypeScript types
└── utils/               # Helper functions
```

### Naming Conventions
- **Components**: PascalCase (`QuestionEditor.tsx`)
- **Utilities**: camelCase (`formatDate.ts`)
- **Types**: PascalCase (`Assignment.ts`)
- **Constants**: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (`MAX_ATTEMPTS`)
- **CSS classes**: kebab-case (`physics-container`)

